title: AP Exclusive: Under Clinton, State's cybersecurity suffered
text: AP Exclusive: Under Clinton, State's cybersecurity suffered   19, 2015 @ 1:56 am \n FILE - In this Aug. 10, 2006, file photo, the sign used as the backdrop for press briefings at the U.S. Department of State is seen before a news conference at the State Department in Washington. The State Department was among the worst agencies in the federal government at protecting its computer networks while Hillary Rodham Clinton was secretary from 2009 to 2013, a situation that continued to deteriorate as John Kerry took office and Russian hackers breached the departmentâs email system, according to independent audits and interviews. (AP Photo/Charles Dharapak, File)\n
